metadata.name: The Blueprint 1
metadata.description:
EDITION 1 OF 1  
 
Title: The Blueprint  
Artist: Godwits  
Year: 2023  
 
"The Blueprint" is an AI collaboration that explores the abstract nature of the intersection of art, engineering, and design. Godwits imagines new possibilities for creative expression in these fields. While there is a sense of structure and order, the works are not intended to solve any problem or serve any practical purpose.  

The absence of any specific function or utilitarian purpose allows the viewer to appreciate the artwork purely on an aesthetic level, free from the constraints of practicality or functionality. It invites the viewer to explore the delicate balance between the precise and the abstract. A beautiful interplay of multiple elements.  

Overall, the works are a celebration of design and engineering for their own sake and ask the age-old question, Is design art? Is a design that is incomplete from utilitarian purpose still evokes feelings or meaning? Is it interesting? What do you think?
